{"id":1776,"date":"2015-10-07T06:00:10","date_gmt":"2015-10-07T13:00:10","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/?p=1776"},"modified":"2015-11-06T02:49:07","modified_gmt":"2015-11-06T10:49:07","slug":"start-screen-shares-directly-from-slack-using-screenleaps-new-slack-integration","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/2015\/10\/07\/start-screen-shares-directly-from-slack-using-screenleaps-new-slack-integration\/","title":{"rendered":"Start Screen Shares Directly From Slack Using Screenleap\u2019s New Slack Integration"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><a href=\"http:\/\/www.slack.com\">Slack<\/a> is a popular tool that lets you chat with your team. If you use Slack, you&#8217;ll be excited to learn that our new integration will make Slack even more useful by allowing your team members to start a screen share directly from within Slack by simply typing \u201c\/leap\u201d into any Slack channel.<\/p>\n<p><strong>How It Works<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Slack offers a number of commands that you can type into the input box to enable additional functionality. Our integration adds a \u201c\/leap\u201d command that you can use to start a screen share directly from within Slack.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/09\/slack_screenleap_slash_command1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1802 size-full\" src=\"http:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/09\/slack_screenleap_slash_command1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"618\" height=\"104\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/09\/slack_screenleap_slash_command1.jpg 618w, https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/09\/slack_screenleap_slash_command1-300x50.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 618px) 100vw, 618px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>You can configure the command by adding additional keywords after the command. Our \u201c\/leap\u201d command supports the following keywords:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>\/leap<\/strong> &#8211; Share your browser window to a private URL.<\/li>\n<li><strong>\/leap screen<\/strong> &#8211; Share your entire screen to a private URL.<\/li>\n<li><strong>\/leap broadcast browser<\/strong> &#8211; Share your browser window to your personal URL.<\/li>\n<li><strong>\/leap broadcast screen<\/strong> &#8211; Share your entire screen to your personal URL.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>You&#8217;ll need to use the Chrome web browser in order to share your screen, but your screen share is viewable by anyone using a device with a web browser, including smartphones and tablets.<\/p>\n<p>Once your screen is shared, the share link will be automatically inserted into your current Slack channel. Your team members will be able to view your screen by simply clicking on the share link.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Integration<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>To add the Screenleap integration to your Slack account, simply click on the &#8220;Add to Slack&#8221; button below:<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/slack.com\/oauth\/authorize?scope=commands&#038;client_id=2359600897.4356494894\" class=\"img\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Add to Slack\" height=\"40\" width=\"139\" src=\"https:\/\/platform.slack-edge.com\/img\/add_to_slack.png\" srcset=\"https:\/\/platform.slack-edge.com\/img\/add_to_slack.png 1x, https:\/\/platform.slack-edge.com\/img\/add_to_slack@2x.png 2x\" style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><\/a><\/p>\n<p>That&#8217;s it! Now everyone on your team will be able to use the \u201c\/leap\u201d command to start a new screen share.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Installation<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>The first time you use the Screenleap slash command, you&#8217;ll be shown a link that you can click on to install the Screenleap browser share extension (if it&#8217;s not already installed).<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/09\/slack_screenleap_installation_link.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1785\" src=\"http:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/09\/slack_screenleap_installation_link.jpg\" alt=\"slack_screenleap_installation_link\" width=\"618\" height=\"60\" style=\"border:0\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/09\/slack_screenleap_installation_link.jpg 618w, https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/09\/slack_screenleap_installation_link-300x29.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 618px) 100vw, 618px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Click on the link to 1) install the browser extension and 2) create a new account (it&#8217;s free!) or sign into your existing Screenleap account. The Free Account gives you 1 hour of free sharing per day (2 hours for people in education). Your screen share will automatically start after the installation completes.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/09\/screenleap_browser_extension_share_menu.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1787\" src=\"http:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/09\/screenleap_browser_extension_share_menu.jpg\" alt=\"screenleap_browser_extension_share_menu\" width=\"618\" height=\"116\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/09\/screenleap_browser_extension_share_menu.jpg 618w, https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/09\/screenleap_browser_extension_share_menu-300x56.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 618px) 100vw, 618px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>As part of the installation, a green screen icon will be added to your Chrome address bar. When you&#8217;re ready to stop your screen share, simply click on the green screen and then click on the \u201cStop sharing\u201d button.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Get In Touch<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>We hope you enjoy the new Slack integration. If you have any questions about the integration or want to learn more about Screenleap, please <a href=\"http:\/\/www.screenleap.com\/support\">contact us<\/a>. We&#8217;d love to hear from you!<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Slack is a popular tool that lets you chat with your team. If you use Slack, you&#8217;ll be excited to learn that our new integration will make Slack even more useful by allowing your team members to start a screen share directly from within Slack by simply typing \u201c\/leap\u201d into any Slack channel. How It [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[2],"tags":[196,197,187,89],"class_list":["post-1776","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-screenleap","tag-enter-screenleap-integration","tag-save-integration","tag-tools","tag-url"],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1776","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=1776"}],"version-history":[{"count":31,"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1776\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":1816,"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1776\/revisions\/1816"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=1776"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/blog.screenleap.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=1776"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/blog.s